Initializing a Repository
After going to the root of your project
Ex. Documents/firstGitProject
(1) git init
Make changes in the desired file (the file being tracked by git)
(2) git add .
(3) git commit -m "Initial Commit"

Process followed:
(1) Make changes
(2) Add the changes
(3) Commit changes to the repository with a message

(*) Writing commit messages
(1) Short summary (less than 50 char)
(2) Optionally followed by blank line and more complete description
(3) Written in present tense

(*) Viewing the commit log
(1) git log
(2) For viewing '5' latest number of commits: git log ~n 5
(3) git log --since=2017-05-01
(4) git log --until=2017-05-01
(5) git log --author="Raghav"
grep -> global regular expression search
(6) git log --grep="Init"
